-- SEC Sues Expert Network Consultants for Giving Insider Tips to Hedge Funds
-- B y   P e t e r   J .   B r e n n a n
-- 2011-02-03T19:01:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-03/sec-sues-expert-network-consultants-for-giving-insider-tips-to-hedge-funds.html
The U.S. Securities and Exchange
Commission said it sued six expert network consultants and
employees for  insider trading  by tipping  hedge funds  and other
investors to generate nearly $6 million. The
information was disclosed in an e-mailed statement.  Four employees of technology companies were moonlighting as
consultants, or “experts” for Primary Global Research LLC
without the knowledge of their employers including Apple Inc.,
Advanced Micro Devices Inc, Dell Inc. and Flextronics
International Ltd., the SEC said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter J. Brennan at 
 pbrennan3@bloomberg.net  